content.text:
Here is what changed.

### What re-running exposed (same issue class as before)

Primary `/build` and `/execute` targets already ran **`mirrorCommittedContentToRepoRoot`** after **`commitToGitHub`**. **`autoWireRoute`** also commits **`startup/register-runtime-routes.js`**, but that second commit did **not** mirror — so chained runs that injected or read **`register-runtime-routes.js`** from disk could still see **stale content** until a redeploy. That gap is fixed by mirroring right after that commit:

```996:1010:/Users/adamhopkins/Projects/Lumin-LifeOS/routes/lifeos-council-builder-routes.js
    // Commit updated file
    await commitToGitHub(
      REGISTER_PATH,
      current,
      `[system-build] wire ${exportName} to register-runtime-routes.js`,
      branch
    );
    const mirrorReg = await mirrorCommittedContentToRepoRoot(REGISTER_PATH, current);
    if (!mirrorReg.ok) {
      log.warn(
        { path: REGISTER_PATH, reason: mirrorReg.reason },
        '[BUILDER] Runtime repo mirror failed after autoWireRoute — chained files[] seeing register-runtime-routes.js may lag until redeploy',
      );
    }
    return { ok: true, exportName, mountPath, committed: true };
```

**Verification:** `node --check routes/lifeos-council-builder-routes.js` passes.

### Honest note on “highest model”

KNOW: Switching Cursor to Opus 4.7 does **not** re-execute server code or change Railway behavior automatically. KNOW: This pass was a deliberate second review of **`lifeos-council-builder-routes.js`**, which turned up **`autoWireRoute`** mirroring plus one more residual inconsistency (**`/execute`** for `.js` does not reuse **`/build`’s `node --check` gate**) — documented under **Known gaps** in **`AMENDMENT_21`** (fix only if bad JS via `/execute` becomes a recurring problem).

### SSOT / continuity

- **`docs/projects/AMENDMENT_21_LIFEOS_CORE.md`**: receipt row, **Last Updated** prefix, Agent Handoff, Known gaps updated.  
- **`docs/CONTINUITY_LOG.md`**: **`[FIX] Update 2026-04-25 #1`** added; **`[FIX] Update 2026-04-29 #2`** bullet about “GitHub-path only autoWire” superseded/corrected.

**Next:** Deploy so production runs **`autoWireRoute`** + mirror together; optionally add response flags (**`route_wiring_mirrored`**) later for debugging.

